Plot the famous Iris data

  1. Here, add a scatter plot of the iris data set depicting Sepal.Length and Sepal.Width variables and print the figure and the code snippet.

how to make iris appear in italic in the title?

ggplot(iris, aes(x=Sepal.Length, y=Sepal.Width, color=Species)) +
geom_point()+
  ggtitle("Sepal size of three *Iris* species") +
labs(
x="Length [cm]",
y="Width [cm]")

Formula

  1. Here, add a formula which calculates the Toxic Unit of a concentration (ci) and and EC50 value together with the corresponding text (see Markdown slides).

\[ sumTU = log10 \left(\sum_{i=1}^n \frac{c_i}{EC_{50_i}} \right) \]

where \[ c_i \] is the concentration of the pesticide i and \[ EC_{50_i}\] is the concentration of pesticide \[i\] at which 50 % of the test organisms (Daphnia magna) were affected.
